    This approach respects architectural boundaries (BusinessModules cannot reference BaseModules).
    
    Changes:
    - ResponseModel: Added RequiresNewToken flag, removed JWT/RefreshToken fields
    - Handler: Removed JWT generation logic (belongs in BaseModules/IAM)
    - DataAccess: Removed IAM-specific methods (GetUserRolesWithModule, AddRefreshToken)
    - Mapper: Simplified to return RequiresNewToken=true
    
    Flow:
    1. POST /AssignInitialRole → UserRole insert + RequiresNewToken=true
    2. Frontend calls POST /Auth/RefreshToken → New JWT with roles
    
    This ensures proper separation of concerns while achieving the same goal:
    users get a JWT with their newly assigned role without logout/login.
    
    Related issue: Initial login JWT lacks role information

